                           <locus target="#12ra">Fol. 12ra</locus>-vb: Excerpt from the hymn ʾƎsäggǝd lä-mäläkotǝkä ...<q xml:lang="gez">Fol. 12ra-vb: በስመ" ... እሰግድ᎓ ለመለኮትከ ... </q>
                           <q xml:lang="en">Fol. 12ra-vb: In the name of the father … I worship Thy Godhead …</q>
                           
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#94r">Fol. 94r</locus>: Donation note.<q xml:lang="gez">Fol. 94r: ዝመፅሐፍ᎓ ዘወሀባ᎓ ለታቦተ᎓ ኪዳነ᎓ ምህረት᎓ አቡነ᎓ ገረመስቀል᎓ ለታቦተ᎓ ኪዳነ᎓ ምህረት᎓ ከመ᎓ ይኩኖ᎓ መርሀ᎓ ለመንግስተ᎓ ሰማያት᎓ መሰለ[sic]᎓ እህቱ᎓ ወለተ᎓  ኪዳን᎓ ወለተ᎓ ወለተ[sic]᎓ ስላሴ᎓ ዘሰረቆ᎓ ወዘፈሀቆ᎓ በስልጣነ᎓ ጴጥሮስ᎓ ወጳውሎስ᎓᎓ ያድህኖ᎓ ውስተ᎓ ሀቄ᎓ ሰነን᎓  </q>
                           <q xml:lang="en">Fol. 94r: This book is which ʾabunä Gärämäsqäl donated to the tabot of Kidanä Mǝhrät so that it might be for him the guide to the Kingdom of Heaven, with his sisters Wälättä Kidan, Wälättä Sǝllase … </q>
                           Crudly written.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a3">
                           <locus target="#94v">Fol. 94v</locus>: Miracle of the Trinity worked “in the land of Ram”. <q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           Written in a recent hand in vivid violet ink.
Gäbrä Täklä Haymanot is mentioned in the supplication formula.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a4">
                           <locus target="#95r">Fol. 95r</locus>: Ownership note. <q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <q xml:lang="en"> </q>
                           The note is crudely written in pencil by Yǝhdägo, the son of Gäbrä Mäsqäl who is the donor of the Ms.
                        </item>
